2022: the year of being truly present in the moment🫶🏻

One of my goals in the new year was to not let the fear of the future control my life like it did in 2021. By letting myself be in the present moment I was able to enjoy every moment for what it was. This year has been one of my favorites by far. @eventful_erin has been my baby this year and I’m so excited to continue to work hard to grow and help others plan more special events. I’m sad to leave 2022 but excited to keep practicing living in the NOW!!!
thanks for being the best part of my year💌

Next Chapter: Charleston, South Carolina🫶🏻🦪🌞

so special for @eventful_erin to help out with @grayforglioblastoma cycling event today 🌟

This organization is very dear to my heart because glioblastoma is the type of brain cancer I lost my grandpa to in the fall. Very special to not only raise money for this specific brain cancer research but also for spreading the word by raising awareness! Thank you to @jibesouth and @katesnedekerr for helping bring us all together for such an important cause! So lucky to have such a great community in charleston!
